# Cursor rules for this repo

- Do not make any changes the user did not explicitly ask for.
- If a helpful improvement is outside the user’s request, propose it first and wait for approval.
- Keep edits narrowly scoped to the requested files/behavior.
- To find “where a feature lives”, start with `@INDEX.md` (file map) and `@docs/FEATURES.md` (product/feature map).
- Keep `INDEX.md` up to date: when adding/removing/moving files, or changing exported APIs/components/pages/routes, update `INDEX.md` in the same change (no exceptions).
- Keep `docs/FEATURES.md` up to date: when adding/changing/removing user-facing features or flows (pages/routes, sharing behavior, upload pipeline, auth/invite gating, AI/review/metrics, admin tools), update `docs/FEATURES.md` in the same change.
- When editing/adding **pages or API routes** (`src/app/**`), ensure the file contains a short top-of-file comment describing purpose and route.
- When editing/adding **libraries** (`src/lib/**`), ensure exported symbols have a short doc comment when non-obvious.


